Prolific producer and ‘Focus’ dance beat originator, Ajimovoix Drums, has started off the year 2022 with a new dance beat titled, ‘Mario Dance Beat’, released on the February 14. Taking inspiration from the video game series Super Mario, the dance beat samples gaming sounds and comes packed with a healthy dose of nostalgia. Mario Dance Beat serves as Ajimovoix Drums’ first single of the year, coming after his Community and Donda Dance Beat, released following the success of Focus Dance Beat, then toped it up with with Cashout Dance Beat, which is currently making waves on social media. As we all know how Ajimovoix drums stormed 2021 with the world trending Focus Dance, he said he’s back to rock and do the same for 2022 and so more. Ajimovoix is the flagbearer of the new age of street-inspired dance music, and he puts his versatility on display with his return.